values:
I want to talk to you on the second, a lot has been going on, I feel horrible, I havent been honest with you and im tired of feeling this way. Nikki, I have been playing the field so to say, I was just curious to see what was out there, you havent seemed interested in me romantically in the slightest and i dunno I was just curious. Something good came of all this though. I realized that there is no one out there. You cared about me when no one did and believed in me when no one else would. I miss you nikki... I want to talk to you when i get home from blacksburg on the second. 

-Michael


What do I do? Help....I found out that this guy at work has it really bad for me. He came over last night because neither one of us had anything else to do and we ended up drinking so he stayed the night and we had a great time. He is not the normal guy that I would go for but he is such a sweetheart and a good guy. I think I like him but I just started to get to know him and I would like to  get to know him better. Like I have said before I am not ready for anouther relationship right now. I don't want to lose Mike as a friend but I have a feeling he is going to want to get back together with me and I just don't want that. He also said that if I started seeing other guys that he is not going to hang around and watch that. I should have never started dateing him in the first place, we should have just stayed friends. So why did I stay with him for so long? And how do I keep him as a friend even though I want to see what is going to happen with Scott (the guy at work).

I'm moved in, all my stuff is here. I stil have tons of unpacking to do but I am here. My apartment-mates are great. One is from England and the other from Scotland. We have been getting along great, granted I have only been here for one day and most of that has been me moveing in. I'm just really excited to be here and not have to be at home listening to my parents argue all the time or to deal with all the crap at home. Anyway, just wanted to give everyone an update about what is going on over here. :D

I don't know what to do, I've been feeling like a complete ass with how I ended it with Mike. I don't know what to do, I feel this need to message him and tell him if he is ready I would like to sit down and talk to him. Explaine things like I should have done the night he came down, but Matt would not quite calling and he wanted to come out side so bad I couldn't say the things that I needed to say. Maybe I did fall for Matt too quickley, maybe I am just feeding off the feelings he has for me and takeing them as my own feelings for him. He is living in my dorm right now, and I don't see him makeing any moves to get anouther apartment. He has stopped talking to me about us getting an apartment together but he hasnt talked to me about him getting one without me either. He does know that my parents are comeing down this weekend for Junior Dad's and the he needs to be gone Thurday night, but he is not makeing any moves to get gone. Also, I think liveing with him so soon is not the best of ideas, I was just getting cought up in the whirlwind of having someone pay so much attention to me and all that after being with Mike who stopped paying attention to me. I just don't know what to do. I want some alone time, I pretty much right now have a roommate and I am not getting any work done. I can't tell him he needs to go because he doesn't have anywhere to go right now. But if I don't then I will continue to not get any work done and I can't afford that at this point in the semester. I want to tell him he should go to California, where he dreams of going to live with his brother and become a cop. But he says he wont leave without me. Well it may take me a while to leave, also I have this whole modeling thing that I want to see what comes of that and I may be traveling all over the world persuing my dream. How is he going to deal with that? He has already told me that there are some photo shoots that he does not want me to ever do, and I am sorry but that is my call not his and if he can't deal with it then we wernt ment to be anyway. He needs to understand that I am not going to put my dreams on hold for him just because he is willing to do the same thing for me. I never asked him to, I told him that he should go and chase his dreams that I will be here. I mean hell if Anja and Alex can make it work with the ociean between them why can't Matt and I make it work across the country? He says he will not leave the state without me, well I may be leaveing the country with out him if I do get signed to an agency. I just don't know what to do. The only thing I know is that he needs to be out of the dorm before my parents get here this weekend. And he can't really come back because I am leaveing for Thanksgiving break after this weekend and then we have finals and then Winter break after that. So he better figure out something.

I know my parents will not be completley happy with this but Matt and I are serously thinking about getting an apartment together. I know that people are saying that it may be too soon, but when you know you have the one you are suppoused to be with forever it is really hard to wait to be together. It's not like I'm giving up school or running off to get married right away, we just want to live together and be together. He understands that school is what I need to be doing right now and he is completly supportive, I mean he has even helped me with my algebra and I actually understand it when he helps. I love him and I want to be with him, and I can't wait to get married one day but that wont be until I am done with school. But yeah, we are looking at getting a place maybe in Staunton or Waynesboro and me moveing in after this semester. Daddy was the one who was all happy and supportive about me getting an apartment with Evie, i think the only problem will be who the apartment is going to be with. Not the fact that I'm getting one. Wish me luck, cause I'm gonna need it.

I can't wait till we are all back at school, I need my girls so much right now. Mike and I are having some problems. He thinks sometimes that he may be holding me back from finding a great guy who is good enough for me, someone who is more settled with their lives someone who is more like me. Also he thinks that when he goes away to school that we are going to have issues with the long distance relationship thing (he is most likely going to go to JMU, not that long distance!) He is worried that we are going to break up when he goes away to school, he is baseing this off of Drew and Rachel because their long distance relationship didn't work. First of all we are not Drew and Rachel, and second of all I am not as crazy as Rachel is not even a little bit. I never really thought about his going to school being a bad thing for the relationship, not until he brought it up at the beach last night. I still think he is crazy. But what has been bothering me is that the more time we spend together the less we have in common. I do love him, I love him a lot; it's just that for all the time we spend together only about an hour a day is he truly acting his age. He acts so immiture (probably spelled wrong), especally when he is around Drew. He's just been really annoying me lately and he has been noticing it too. Last time he noticed me getting irritated with him he freaked out and broke up with me. I almost thought he was gonna do that last night while we were talking on the beach. I don't want to break up with him and I don't want him to break up with me, but I think something needs to change or maybe.....I don't know, I just don't know what to do.

Harry Potter....IMAX.....final fight scene in 3D....it was so amazing....
I love Harry Potter movies!!!!!

Can't wait till next monday.....BEACH TRIP!!!!
I so need a vacation

I start work today. I'm a server at Red Robin here in C-ville, I'm really nervous and I'm sick. It is the worst to be sick during the summer. 

Nothing else much really going on here. I am spending tons of time with Mike now that I have my car back. It is weird to be driving again, but I am loving the freedom. 

Well, I better go take a shower and start getting ready for work. Wish me luck, I think I'm gonna need it. lol

I GOT MY CAR BACK!!!  I CAN DRIVE NOW! I CAN GET A JOB AND START MAKEING MONEY!! I'LL HAVE MY CAR FOR NEXT YEAR!! 

life is good

well except the fact that while Mike was fixing my car he some how made the check engine light turn on and it wont go away. Mike says that it is nothing so not to worry....yeah right, me not worry.

So far this summer hasnt been too bad. Today is monday and I have been at Mike's house since thursday and I wont be leaving till tomorrow evening. Also I will finally be getting my car back, hopefully, by the end of this week, which means I will be getting a job. I am curious if I will actually get a roommate next year at school since my roomie wont be comming back. I was thinking about not comming back to Baldwin next year myself. I havent been really happy there and everyone has heard me at some point say how much I hate school and I hate being there, or how much I hate being home. I was thinking I would get an apartment in C-ville and getting a full time job and just takeing a couple classes at Piedmont; but I don't think I will do that. So far things have cooled down and this summer is starting to look like I can get through it and next semester is the first one I have been looking forward to since I started college. I think I just needed to get out of the slump I was in. Although I did take a step back in my personal achievements, that I overcame this past semester, the second week I was home. But that's ok, it all worked out in the end. So for now things are going well. I really want to get together with some people from school before the summer is over. I miss you all.

So, I just finished my final and I think I did pretty well. I am sad to be leaveing Baldwin, I'm gonna miss it here, and the people....well...some of them.  It has been a interesting year, filled with tears, pain, love, happiness, all the usual stuff.  School could have been better but oh well, I'll make up for that later.  I don't want to be going home, I kinda pretty much hate Buckingham but it's ok becuase I'll be getting my car back as soon as possible. :D I can't wait.  This summer is going to be fun though, I'm planning on getting a job again (I can't wait!!!) I have missed working; also, I'm going to be spending a lot of time with Mike (as usual) and the rest of his group.  It's going to be an awsome summer...you know, except for that whole Buckingham thing. But I'm staying positive and excited about it all.  The Rents are comming down tomorrow to help me pack and move out, then only three and a half months before I get to come back to Baldwin. I hate packing, It's not that packing is hard, it's just annoying. Moving in is so much better than moving out. 
Well, I guess thats it for now. See you all next year, hope you all have wonderful summers and all that good stuff. Love you all.....well most of you :P

It SNOWED!! It was so warm this past week and it snows tonight. WHY? I want spring, it was so pretty out. We were all wearing skirts and tanktops and all thoes spring clothes. And it just up and left us. That is not a nice thing to do at all. 
Where did spring go?
I think winter was upset that its time had ended for this year that it kidnapped spring and decided that winter should have a longer time to rule the world. Winter had its time, we want spring. Please winter bring back spring!!!!

Ok who hasn't been in a library before? The rule is that libraries are suppoused to be quiet. Obiviously these peopel missed the memo. Becuase they are talking at full volume, and since our library only has students working in it there is no one to tell them to shut up. There are six people working here and they are all too busy playing on the computers to do anything about the noise. Oh and what the hell is up with talking on cell phones in the library? They should have a no cell phone sign. People are idoits! I have been trying to write a paper for about an hour and I have less than half a page because it is too loud in here. The funny thing about all this is that my paper is for my philosophy class and I have to decide which philosopher I most agree with about human nature. And the longer I am in here with these stupid people, who don't understand that people come to the library for quite to do their work, the more I am leaning toward Schopenhauer who has a very pessimistic view of human nature. So my paper is going to be all "Humans suck! For the most part they are so stupid! They can not even follow simple rules. We should restrict breeding so only the smart ones are allowed to have children. And that cuts out the people with whom I share the library tonight." 

Why do they have to be so loud?

You are The Moon

Hope, expectation, Bright promises.

The Moon is a card of magic and mystery - when prominent you know that nothing is as it seems, particularly when it concerns relationships. All logic is thrown out the window.

The Moon is all about visions and illusions, madness, genius and poetry. This is a card that has to do with sleep, and so with both dreams and nightmares. It is a scary card in that it warns that there might be hidden enemies, tricks and falsehoods. But it should also be remembered that this is a card of great creativity, of powerful magic, primal feelings and intuition. You may be going through a time of emotional and mental trial; if you have any past mental problems, you must be vigilant in taking your medication but avoid drugs or alcohol, as abuse of either will cause them irreparable damage. This time however, can also result in great creativity, psychic powers, visions and insight. You can and should trust your intuition.

So today I turned 19 and all I wanna do right now is go home. My dad would have cooked me a great birthday meal, anything I would want, most likely STEAK (yum). My mom would have made me a cake with candles and everything. The whole day would be about me, god I miss being at home. My girls have been great today about it being my birthday, having everyone at lunch and dinner, but there is nothing like a brithday at home with all the traditions of home. 
~
Life is moving on, very fast. It seems like yesterday I was beging my Senior year in high school, hanging out with Steph, James, and Charlie all night (and getting in so much trouble doing it). Then I had turned 18, talk about a mile stone in someone's life. I had lived 18 years and seen so many things, been through so many things in my life. And before I knew it I was graduating from high school. Everyone knows how important that is. I still can't belieave that they actually let me graduate. Summer flew by and bam it hit me....I was starting my freshman year in COLLEGE. I was so scared, I didn't know what to expect. I was sure that I wouldn't make any friends that no one would like me. But I was wrong, I made 5 of the best friends anyone could ever ask for. The are more like my sisters instead of my friends. We do everything together, god do we have fun. We will be friends for a long time, and the memories that we have made this year will last us forever. I will never forget them or what we have been through this year. I finished my first semester in college, and did ok. I could have done a lot better but give me a break it was my first semester. I have gotten in to trouble, been to clubs, met guys, and gotten drunk. So, now I'm 19. Looking back this has been a very busy and life altering year. I have learned so much about myself and the world around me. And with all the headachs, heartachs, and tears, I would do it all over again. I loved every min. of it, and I can't wait to see what is to come in this new year of my life. What I do know is my sisters will be there with me to celebrate everyday of it.

I had the best morning ever!! It started out with a fun night out, with Drew, Anja, Evie, and I. We went clubbing, which is always fun, if you can find a nice guy to dance with, and Evie and I did. Then when the club was closing we saw them walking (we were in my car), the guys and all of us agreed to meet up at SHEETS. Well the next move was theirs, they invited Evie and I to go ridding with them (we were gonna go 4-wheelen, but there wasn't enough snow). Any way, Evie and I agree (after makeing sure it was ok with Anja and Drew, Anja and Drew took my car back to the dorms, and Evie and I went for an amazing adventure. We had alcohol, two cute boys, and we were sitting on top of a mountain (with a beautiful view). We had so much fun, and I am pretty sure we are gonna see Brian and Chad again, soon........(I hope I will see Brian again). "GREAT ADVICE"

Don't date because you are desperate.
Don't marry because you are miserable.
Don't have kids because you think your genes are superior. 
Don't philander because you think you are irresistible.

Don't associate with people you can't trust.
Don't cheat. Don't lie. Don't pretend.
Don't dictate because you are smarter.
Don't demand because you are stronger.

Don't sleep around because you think you are old enough and know better.
Don't hurt your kids because loving them is harder. 
Don't sell yourself, your family, or your ideals. 
Don't stagnate.

Don't regress.
Don't live in the past. Time can't bring anything or anyone back. 
Don't put your life on hold for possibly Mr/Mrs Right. 
Don't throw your life away on absolutely Mr Wrong because your biological clock is ticking.

Learn a new skill.
Find a new friend.
Start a new career.
Sometimes, there is no race to be won. 
Only a price to be paid for some of life's more hasty decisions.

To terminate your loneliness, reach out to the homeless.
To feed your nurturing instincts, care for the needy.
To fulfill your parenting fantasies, get a puppy.
Don't bring another life into this world for all the wrong reasons.

To make yourself happy, pursue your passions and be the best of what you can be. Simplify your life. Take away the clutter. 
Get rid of destructive elements: abusive friends, nasty habits, and dangerous liaisons. 
Don't abandon your responsibilities but don't overdose on duty.

Don't live life recklessly without thought and feeling for your family.
Be true to yourself. Don't commit when you are not ready. 
Don't keep others waiting needlessly.

Go on that trip. Don't postpone it.
Say those words. Don't let the moment pass.
Do what you have to, even at society's scorn.

Write poetry.
Love Deeply.
Walk barefoot.
Dance with wild abandon.
Cry at the movies.

Take care of yourself. Don't wait for someone to take care of you. 
You light up your life. You drive yourself to your destination. 
No one completes you - except YOU.

It is true that life does not get easier with age. It only gets more challenging. 
Don't be afraid. Don't lose your capacity to love. Pursue your passions.

Live your dreams.
Don't lose faith in your God.
Don't grow old. Just grow YOU!

~ Unknown

You Know You're From a Small Town When...
The "road hog" in front of you on Main Street is a farmer's combine. The local phone book has only one yellow page. Third Street is on the edge of town. You leave your jacket on the back of the chair in the cafe, and when you go back the next day, it's still there, on the same chair. You don't signal turns because everyone knows where you're going, anyway. No social events can be scheduled when the school gym floor is being varnished. You call a wrong number and they supply you with the correct one. Everyone knows all the news before it's published; they just read the hometown paper to see whether the publisher got it right. The city limits signs are both on the same post! The City jail is called amoeba, because it only has one cell. The McDonalds only has one Golden Arch. The one-block-long Main Street dead ends in both directions. Second Street is in the next town over. There's no place to go that you shouldn't. A "Night on the Town" takes only 11 minutes. The mayor had to annex property to eat a foot-long hot dog. The New Year's baby was born in October. Running from the cops consists of hiding in the cornfield. You have to name six surrounding towns to explain to people where you're from. You have to drive five miles out in the country to smoke a cigarette. Headline news is who grew the biggest vegetable this year. There is no point in high-school reunions because everyone knows what everyone else is doing anyway. Driving cars up and down the main drag is a universal high school experience. You can name everyone you graduated with. You know what 4-H is. You ever went to parties at a pasture, barn, or in the middle of a dirt road. You said the 'f' word and your parents knew within the hour. You schedule parties around the schedule of different police officers, since you know which ones would bust you and which ones wouldn't - same goes with the game warden. You ever went cow-tipping or snipe hunting. School gets canceled for state sporting events. You could never buy cigarettes because all the store clerks knew how old you were and if you were old enough, they would still tell your folks. When you did find someone old enough and brave enough to buy cigarettes, you still had to go out to the country and drive back roads to smoke them. You were ever in the Homecoming parade. You have ever gone home for Homecoming. It was cool to date someone from the neighboring town. You had senior skip day. The whole school went to the same party after graduation. You don't give directions by street names or references (turn by Nelson's house, go two blocks to the Anderson's turn left and it's four houses left of the football field). The golf course had only 9 holes You can't help but date a friend's ex-girlfriend. Your car stays filthy because of the dirt roads, and you will never own a dark vehicle for this reason. You think kids that ride skateboards are weird. The town next to you is considered "trashy" or "snooty" but is actually just like your town. Getting paid minimum wage is considered a great job. You refer to anyone with a house newer than 1980 as "rich" people. The people in the city dress funny, then you pick up on the trend a few years later. You bragged to your friends because you got pipes on your truck for your birthday. Anyone you want can be found at either the Dairy Queen or the feed store. You see at least one friend a week driving a tractor through town. Football coaches suggest that you haul hay for the summer to get stronger. Directions are given using "the" stop light as a reference The city council meets at the coffee shop. Your letter jacket was worn after your 19th birthday. You have ever taken a trailer or dog to school on a daily basis. Weekend excitement involves a trip to the grocery store. Even the ugly people enter beauty contests. You decide to walk somewhere for exercise and 5 people pull over and ask if you need a ride. Your teachers call you by your older siblings names. Your teachers remember when they taught your parents. You can charge at all the local stores. The closest McDonald's is 45 miles away. So is the closest mall. It is normal to see an old man riding through town on a riding lawn mower. Everyone who played sports had to play on every type of team, or there wouldn't be enough people to have a team. Being able to hit a road sign with a beer bottle while driving down the highway is considered a necessary skill. A cool vehicle had big tires or a bad-ass stereo. You can remember when your town finally got cable. Driving to the party on a four wheeler is quite normal. You thought the 30-year-old guy that still was at all the parties was cool. The town population increases by one-third when the universities go on break. The best burgers in town are at the rink. You know exactly where to go when the party is at "the lake". You lost your virginity at a bush party. You actually get these jokes and pass them on to other friends from a small town.

It is a weird feeling when you suddenly see everything you wanted start to faid away. I know what I dream in life and I have always been really optimistic about reaching my dreams, but now I can't see them so clearly now. I don't know what my future holds, I don't know what I am going to do about anything. I want to be the same person I was before, but that is not possible. I feel like I am losing myself, I don't know what to do. I want to see if I could make it out there in the world, but I everything I try to do just doesn't come through like I wanted it to. Nothing turns out right. I have always said to hold on to your dreams, but now.... Not so much anymore, it is to hard to see that it could never happen. That I have always dreamed too big for me. I was trying to say I could do anything, but now I am growing up and I see that there are things that are just not possible. Things that I saw myself doing in the past, I know I will never get the chance to do. It is not worth the effort anymore to dream. My hopes just get to high, and everytime I could see how something could work, it doesn't come through. I want so bad to be a model, an actress, and a singer, but I know that it will never be true. I will never be anything that I used to see myself being. Only by a merical will I get to do anything of thoes things. As it is now, I don't see me being anything special. My dreams are faiding away and I don't know what to do anymore. I don't know how to bring my dreams back. I don't know how to react to what is going on inside me. I don't want to lose my hope, but I can see it leaving....very quickly. Why is it when we get older, all our dreams leave us? I don't want to know the truth, that the possibility of me being famous is slim to none. I want to have the faith I used to have. I want to be the old Nicole again. I don't want to be the person I see now. I want to be someone else, I don't know how to deal with the person I am now. I see me and I don't see how I became this way. I have had terrible things done to me in the past, things that are truly unfair and that I shouldn't have had to go through, and I keep pushing those thing further and further back in my heart and head. As if they didn't happen or that I just can't deal with them anymore. The strong person who I used to be is faiding away fast. I used to be able to handle my family and make everything better, now I don't know what to do. I am lost, and I can't seem to find my way back to me. I want to be whole, but I have lost a vital part of Nicole. I don't feel like Nicole anymore. What people see everyday is just a shell. A shell of what I used to be. I am changing, and with what I can tell, it is not the best kind of change. It's not fair, I was just starting to like Nicole, and then I lose her. I have so many feelings inside me that I can't show, no one would understand. I just want to be someone else right now, I don't even want to be the same Nicole I used to be. I don't think that I could ever be the same again. Too many things have happened, but I don't want to be who I am becoming. I'm loseing too many things about myself. Too many things were stolen from me.
